HEADWORD: Pulpiteer
<hw>Pul*pit*eer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who speaks in
a pulpit; a preacher; -- so called in contempt.</def>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We never can think it sinful that Burns should have been humorous
on such a <qex>pulpiteer</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Prof.
Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pulpiter</ent>⟦br⟧
